      "author": {
        "id": 934
      },
      "writtenOn": "2013-11-26T10:20:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I absolutely did not want to expose the CanonicalTreeParsers to the custom merge drivers. I do not wish to give implementers a mean to totally break the merging. With the tree parsers, an implementer could break something while telling us all went well : ignoring files, corrupting the index...\n\nNot to mention that it makes implementing a custom driver _much_ more difficult. Users shouldn\u0027t need to understand how to use the JGit innards in order to implement a merger for their custom file formats.\n\nFinally, I wish to remain as close as possible to the \"merge drivers\" as defined in Git itself ( https://www.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/gitattributes.html#_performing_a_three_way_merge ) : it wouldn\u0027t do to have our own merge drivers totally differing from the merge drivers as known by other git implementations : users who stumble on these documents (or those that are used to these mechanisms) should be able to understand how to do things.",
